FitnessUniformSelection
Fitness Uniform Selection is a selection strategy that chooses chromosomes based on a randomly generated target fitness value within the current fitness range.

Interface for mutation operators in a genetic algorithm.

Master
Master class that distributes chromosomes among multiple threads (workers) for parallel fitness evaluation.

A mutation operator that applies mutation with a probability that decreases over generations.

An implementation of the Order Crossover (OX) operator.

Represents a population of chromosomes in a genetic algorithm.

An implementation of a probabilistic crossover operator.
RandomRepleacmentTournament
RandomReplacementTournament is a selection method where a tournament of a fixed size is held, and the best chromosome is usually selected.
RouleteElitismSelection
RouletteElitismSelection combines roulette wheel selection with elitism.
RouletteWheelSelection
RouletteWheelSelection implements a probabilistic selection method based on fitness proportion.
ScrambleMutation
A mutation operator that applies a scrambling mutation to a selected portion of a chromosome.
SinglePointCrossOver
Implements the classic singlepoint crossover operator.
SinglePointMutation
A mutation operator that applies a singlepoint mutation to a chromosome.
SwapMutation
Swap mutaion performs a mutation on a chromosome by swapping two randomly selected genes within the chromosome.

TournamentSelection implements the tournament selection method.

The TwoPointMutation class applies a mutation by altering two distinct genes at randomly selected positions within the chromosome.
